title: Astronaut Catherine Bunnell-Pegg named Australian of the Year | 7NEWS
description: Catherine Bunnell-Pegg, an astronaut from Adelaide who became the first Australian to qualify for space travel under the nation's flag in 2024, has been named Australian of the Year for 2026. Olympic champion Cathy Freeman received the nation's highest honour as a Companion of the Order of Australia. Other recipients include dementia researcher Harry Bredatti as Senior Australian of the Year, Indigenous employment advocate Frank Mitchell as Local Hero, and endurance runner Ned Brockman as Young Australian of the Year. title: Minneapolis erupts after second fatal ICE shooting | 7NEWS
description: Federal immigration agents shot and killed 37-year-old Alex Preti, a local ICU nurse in Minneapolis, after he attempted to help a woman pushed over by a Border Patrol agent. The incident, captured on video from multiple angles, shows Preti being wrestled to the ground and struck before being fatally shot, despite no evidence he reached for his legally permitted firearm. This marks the second fatal shooting by ICE agents in Minneapolis within weeks, following the death of local mother Renee Goode, prompting the state governor to demand the immediate withdrawal of 3,000 federal immigration agents from the city.
